22 register with the secretary of state each year during which the candidate holds public
23 office or during which the political committee receives contributions, makes
24 expenditures for political purposes, or has a balance in the campaign account. An
25 individual who no longer holds public office or an individual who no longer seeks public
26 office shall register with the secretary of state each year in which contributions are
27 deposited, expenditures are made for political purposes, or a balance remains in the
28 campaign account.
